We examined the stomach gross anatomy of one juvenile specimen (CNP 895 ). The morphology is of the type unilocular hemiglandular (see Carleton, 1973 ); in this morphology the glandular epithelium from the antrum extends to the corpus, near the esophagus opening (
Fig. 8
). Measures of the thick intestine and caecum are 3.5 and 1.8 cm , respectively.
